[3] Cholera - Nigeria (Nasarawa State)
Date: Wed 20 Dec 2017
Source: The Cable [edited]
https://www.thecable.ng/four-killed-fresh-cholera-outbreak-nasarawa


At least 4 persons have died in a fresh outbreak of cholera in Nasarawa state. The victims, who were from Shege, a village in Toto local government area of the state, were said to have died before they could reach the only primary healthcare center in the community. The Cable learnt that among those killed were a mother and her daughter.

According to a resident, people of the community have always "appealed to the state government for provision of motorized borehole [a well] to curb the spread of water-borne diseases."

Musa Abdullahi, public relations officer of the state ministry of health, said the situation is under control from spreading to other communities.

